FBIS4-46169 "jptot022__l94078" JPRS-TOT-94-022-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 27 May 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus `Terrorists' Seize 30 Hostages on Board Bus in North Caucasus Further on Helicopter Takeoff LD2705070394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0647 GMT 27 May 94 LD2705070394 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Excerpt] Mineralniye Vody, May 27 (ITAR-TASS) -- The four gunmen, who hijacked a bus with 26 people in the North Caucasus on Thursday, flew off in a helicopter provided by Russian authorities on Friday after a night of negotiations, carrying away with them three women, two men and the bus driver to an unknown destination. A crew of three is piloting the helicopter. "It looks as if it could be Makhachkala," an Interior Ministry official said. The helicopter is being accompanied by seven military helicopters which keep at a distance from the hijackers. [passage omitted]
